The National Super Alliance is also crowding the IEBC, writing it elaborate memoranda that are designed to play to the Opposition gallery and asking ostensibly searching questions that are in fact designed to result in self-incrimination.Now the IEBC finds itself with neither ballot papers nor the integrated electoral system ICTs that are essential to the holding of the general election. In large swathes of Kenya where the Opposition holds sway, the IEBC finds itself losing credibility by the day arising from NASA&rsquo;s aggressive and innuendo-laden lines of questioning. This sort of thing has not happened to any other electoral commission this close to a general election in recent history anywhere, and certainly never in Kenya. Something has to give. The IEBC must be given the time and space to deliver o